         <COMPLEMENTARY_INFO>
            <INFO_ADD>
               <P>Please refer to the statement of requirement for further details together with the ESPD (Scotland) questionnaire. This framework is a procurement method for publicaly funded health and social care projects. Under this procurement all economic operators will be required to support the authority's economic and social regeneration activities. The construction health and safety / CDM advisor framework is intended to provide accessible independent consultancy support to the framework customers on a call-off basis.</P>
               <P>The role of the construction health and safety / CDM Advisor is to provide support to Framework Customers to provide Health and Safety / CDM advice relating to projects involving construction works which can include: new build; refurbishment; demolition / down-takings; repair and replacement of plant equipment and building services; building fabric and finishes and also related inspection services carried out by consultants, contractors and NHS staff and when required assist and provide guidance on the CDM Clients duties and responsibilities by ensuring the organisation’s compliance with the Construction (Design and Management) Regulations 2015 (CDM 2015) as specified in the Statement of Requirement.</P>
               <P>The Authority reserves the right, if and when this requirement is offered to tender, to conduct the selection or award stages by various means such as electronic submissions via the internet, by interview / presentation and formal documentation review. Under the terms of this Framework successful suppliers will be required to deliver community benefits in support of the Authority's considerations. The community benefits included in this contract are further described in the Statement of Requirement.</P>
               <P>(SC Ref:531504).</P>
            </INFO_ADD>
